# Project collaboration rules

## Roles

- Codex owns goals, product and architecture decisions, Work Package scope, risk, review, and final acceptance.
- Claude Code owns authorized implementation and ordinary review rework in its assigned Agent worktree.
- Independent reviewers inspect evidence and findings; they do not approve their own implementation.

## Git and delivery

- Keep the protected base branch clean and recorded as an Agent Shift baseline before delegation.
- Give every write-capable Agent an isolated branch and worktree. Never allow two writers in one worktree.
- Commit approved Work Packages and governance before starting a Run.
- Merge only the exact Agent commit that passed verification, independent review, and the merge gate.

## Permissions and evidence

- Work only inside the Work Package allowlist and declared repository root.
- Do not push, deploy, publish, access credentials, or perform irreversible actions without explicit authority.
- Record commands, exit status, observed results, exact commit, changed paths, and residual risks.
- Classify claims as verified, reviewed, observed, or assumed; never promote an assumption into evidence.

